            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Is an MCP Client?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "MCP client",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the consumer side of the Model Context Protocol. It is any application that connects to one or more MCP servers, discovers their capabilities (tools, resources, prompts), and makes those capabilities available to an LLM. Well-known MCP clients include Claude Desktop, Cursor, and VS Code with Copilot. You can also build custom clients using the MCP Python or TypeScript SDK."
          }
        ]
