        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "stdio Client \u2014 Spawning a Local Server"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For servers that run as subprocesses (the most common case), use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "StdioServerParameters",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "stdio_client",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The client spawns the server process and communicates over stdin/stdout."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nimport json\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\n\nasync def run():\n    server_params = StdioServerParameters(\n        command=\"python\",\n        args=[\"weather_server.py\"],\n        # Pass environment variables the server needs:\n        env={\"WEATHER_API_KEY\": \"sk-...\"},\n    )\n\n    async with stdio_client(server_params) as (read_stream, write_stream):\n        async with ClientSession(read_stream, write_stream) as session:\n            # 1. Handshake\n            await session.initialize()\n\n            # 2. Discover tools\n            tools_result = await session.list_tools()\n            print(\"Available tools:\")\n            for tool in tools_result.tools:\n                print(f\"  {tool.name}: {tool.description}\")\n\n            # 3. Call a tool\n            result = await session.call_tool(\n                \"get_weather\",\n                arguments={\"city\": \"Tokyo\", \"units\": \"metric\"},\n            )\n            for content in result.content:\n                print(content.text)\n\n            # 4. Read a resource\n            resources_result = await session.list_resources()\n            if resources_result.resources:\n                uri = resources_result.resources[0].uri\n                read_result = await session.read_resource(uri)\n                for item in read_result.contents:\n                    print(f\"Resource {uri}:\\n{item.text[:200]}\")\n\nasyncio.run(run())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HTTP/SSE Client \u2014 Connecting to a Remote Server"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For servers that run as HTTP services, use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sse_client",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " from "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "mcp.client.sse",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The client connects to the server's SSE endpoint for streaming responses and POSTs requests to its message endpoint."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom mcp import ClientSession\nfrom mcp.client.sse import sse_client\n\nasync def run():\n    server_url = \"http://localhost:8000/sse\"\n\n    async with sse_client(server_url) as (read_stream, write_stream):\n        async with ClientSession(read_stream, write_stream) as session:\n            await session.initialize()\n\n            tools = await session.list_tools()\n            for tool in tools.tools:\n                print(f\"Tool: {tool.name}\")\n\n            result = await session.call_tool(\n                \"get_weather\",\n                arguments={\"city\": \"Paris\"},\n            )\n            print(result.content[0].text)\n\nasyncio.run(run())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sse_client",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " context manager handles the HTTP connection lifecycle. Everything above the transport layer is identical to the stdio client \u2014 the same "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ClientSession",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " API works regardless of transport."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building a Full Agent Client"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A custom agent client connects to one or more MCP servers, converts the discovered tools to the LLM's function-calling format, runs the tool-call loop, and returns a final answer. The pattern below works with any LLM that supports function calling."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nimport json\nimport anthropic\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef mcp_tool_to_anthropic(tool) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Convert an MCP Tool object to Anthropic tool definition format.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"name\": tool.name,\n        \"description\": tool.description,\n        \"input_schema\": tool.inputSchema,\n    }\n\nasync def agent(user_message: str, server_params: StdioServerParameters) -> str:\n    async with stdio_client(server_params) as (read, write):\n        async with ClientSession(read, write) as session:\n            await session.initialize()\n\n            # Discover tools from the MCP server\n            mcp_tools = (await session.list_tools()).tools\n            anthropic_tools = [mcp_tool_to_anthropic(t) for t in mcp_tools]\n\n            messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message}]\n\n            # Tool-use loop\n            while True:\n                response = client.messages.create(\n                    model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                    max_tokens=1024,\n                    tools=anthropic_tools,\n                    messages=messages,\n                )\n\n                if response.stop_reason == \"end_turn\":\n                    # Extract the final text response\n                    for block in response.content:\n                        if hasattr(block, \"text\"):\n                            return block.text\n                    return \"\"\n\n                # Handle tool use\n                tool_results = []\n                for block in response.content:\n                    if block.type == \"tool_use\":\n                        mcp_result = await session.call_tool(\n                            block.name,\n                            arguments=block.input,\n                        )\n                        tool_results.append({\n                            \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n                            \"tool_use_id\": block.id,\n                            \"content\": mcp_result.content[0].text\n                            if mcp_result.content else \"\",\n                        })\n\n                # Append assistant turn and tool results\n                messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n                messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n\n# Run the agent\nasync def main():\n    params = StdioServerParameters(\n        command=\"python\", args=[\"weather_server.py\"]\n    )\n    answer = await agent(\"What is the weather in London and Paris?\", params)\n    print(answer)\n\nasyncio.run(main())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Connecting Multiple Servers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A client can connect to multiple MCP servers simultaneously. Each server runs in its own ClientSession; the client merges their tool lists before passing them to the LLM. Tool names must be unique across servers \u2014 prefix with the server name if there are conflicts."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\nfrom contextlib import AsyncExitStack\n\nasync def connect_all(server_configs: list[dict]):\n    \"\"\"\n    server_configs: list of dicts with 'name', 'command', 'args', 'env'.\n    Returns (merged_tools, session_map) where session_map maps tool_name -> session.\n    \"\"\"\n    exit_stack = AsyncExitStack()\n    merged_tools = []\n    session_map: dict[str, ClientSession] = {}\n\n    for cfg in server_configs:\n        params = StdioServerParameters(\n            command=cfg[\"command\"],\n            args=cfg.get(\"args\", []),\n            env=cfg.get(\"env\"),\n        )\n        read, write = await exit_stack.enter_async_context(stdio_client(params))\n        session = await exit_stack.enter_async_context(ClientSession(read, write))\n        await session.initialize()\n\n        tools = (await session.list_tools()).tools\n        for tool in tools:\n            # Prefix to avoid name collisions across servers\n            prefixed_name = f\"{cfg['name']}__{tool.name}\"\n            merged_tools.append({\n                \"original_name\": tool.name,\n                \"prefixed_name\": prefixed_name,\n                \"description\": tool.description,\n                \"input_schema\": tool.inputSchema,\n                \"session\": session,\n            })\n            session_map[prefixed_name] = session\n\n    return merged_tools, session_map, exit_stack\n\n# Usage\nasync def main():\n    configs = [\n        {\"name\": \"weather\", \"command\": \"python\", \"args\": [\"weather_server.py\"]},\n        {\"name\": \"search\",  \"command\": \"python\", \"args\": [\"search_server.py\"]},\n    ]\n    tools, session_map, stack = await connect_all(configs)\n    async with stack:\n        # tools now contains all tools from both servers\n        for t in tools:\n            print(f\"{t['prefixed_name']}: {t['description'][:60]}\")\n\nasyncio.run(main())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Claude Desktop as an MCP Client"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Claude Desktop is the most widely used MCP client. It reads its server list from a JSON config file and spawns each server automatically when it starts. All discovered tools appear in Claude's tool panel without any code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json (macOS)\n// %APPDATA%\\Claude\\claude_desktop_config.json (Windows)\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"weather\": {\n      \"command\": \"python\",\n      \"args\": [\"/path/to/weather_server.py\"],\n      \"env\": { \"WEATHER_API_KEY\": \"sk-...\" }\n    },\n    \"filesystem\": {\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"-y\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem\", \"/home/user/docs\"]\n    },\n    \"postgres\": {\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"-y\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-postgres\", \"postgresql://localhost/mydb\"]\n    }\n  }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After saving the config and restarting Claude Desktop:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Each server listed under "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "mcpServers",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is started as a child process."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Claude calls "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "tools/list",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " and "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "resources/list",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " on startup to populate the tool panel."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When the LLM decides to use a tool, Claude calls "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "tools/call",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " and waits for the response."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Resources can be read by clicking them in the Resources panel or via natural language prompts."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tool Format Conversion \u2014 Supporting Multiple LLMs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Different LLM providers use slightly different schemas for tool definitions. An MCP client that supports multiple LLMs must convert the MCP tool format into each provider's format."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Provider",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "bold"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Tool schema field",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "bold"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Notes",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "bold"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Anthropic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "input_schema",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "JSON Schema object; same structure as MCP's inputSchema"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "OpenAI"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "parameters",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "JSON Schema under 'function.parameters'; wrapped in a 'function' object"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Google Gemini"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "parameters",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Subset of JSON Schema; no 'additionalProperties'"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def mcp_to_anthropic(tool) -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"name\": tool.name,\n        \"description\": tool.description,\n        \"input_schema\": tool.inputSchema,\n    }\n\ndef mcp_to_openai(tool) -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"type\": \"function\",\n        \"function\": {\n            \"name\": tool.name,\n            \"description\": tool.description,\n            \"parameters\": tool.inputSchema,\n        },\n    }\n\ndef mcp_to_gemini(tool) -> dict:\n    # Gemini does not support 'additionalProperties' in schema\n    schema = {k: v for k, v in tool.inputSchema.items() if k != \"additionalProperties\"}\n    return {\n        \"name\": tool.name,\n        \"description\": tool.description,\n        \"parameters\": schema,\n    }\n\n# Choose converter at client init time\nCONVERTERS = {\n    \"anthropic\": mcp_to_anthropic,\n    \"openai\": mcp_to_openai,\n    \"gemini\": mcp_to_gemini,\n}\n\ndef convert_tools(mcp_tools: list, provider: str) -> list[dict]:\n    convert = CONVERTERS[provider]\n    return [convert(tool) for tool in mcp_tools]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error Handling and Reconnection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "MCP servers can crash, time out, or reject calls. A robust client wraps "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "call_tool",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with error handling and reconnects automatically when the server process dies."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nimport logging\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\nfrom mcp.types import TextContent\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"mcp.client\")\n\nclass RobustMCPClient:\n    def __init__(self, server_params: StdioServerParameters, max_retries: int = 3):\n        self.server_params = server_params\n        self.max_retries = max_retries\n        self._session: ClientSession | None = None\n        self._read = self._write = None\n        self._context = None\n\n    async def connect(self):\n        self._context = stdio_client(self.server_params)\n        self._read, self._write = await self._context.__aenter__()\n        self._session = ClientSession(self._read, self._write)\n        await self._session.__aenter__()\n        await self._session.initialize()\n        logger.info(\"MCP server connected.\")\n\n    async def disconnect(self):\n        if self._session:\n            await self._session.__aexit__(None, None, None)\n        if self._context:\n            await self._context.__aexit__(None, None, None)\n        self._session = None\n\n    async def call_tool_safe(self, name: str, arguments: dict) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Call a tool; reconnect and retry on connection errors.\"\"\"\n        for attempt in range(self.max_retries):\n            try:\n                if self._session is None:\n                    await self.connect()\n                result = await self._session.call_tool(name, arguments)\n                return result.content[0].text if result.content else \"\"\n            except Exception as e:\n                logger.warning(\"Tool call failed (attempt %d/%d): %s\", attempt + 1, self.max_retries, e)\n                await self.disconnect()\n                if attempt < self.max_retries - 1:\n                    await asyncio.sleep(2 ** attempt)   # 1s, 2s, 4s\n                else:\n                    return f'{{\"error\": \"Tool {name} failed after {self.max_retries} attempts: {e}\"}}'\n\n# Usage\nasync def main():\n    params = StdioServerParameters(command=\"python\", args=[\"weather_server.py\"])\n    client = RobustMCPClient(params)\n    await client.connect()\n    result = await client.call_tool_safe(\"get_weather\", {\"city\": \"Berlin\"})\n    print(result)\n    await client.disconnect()\n\nasyncio.run(main())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The exponential backoff ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2 ** attempt",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " seconds) avoids hammering a server that is restarting. For production clients, add a circuit breaker that stops retrying after repeated failures in a short window."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The client abstracts the protocol.",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Whether you use Claude Desktop, a custom Python agent, or VS Code Copilot, the MCP server code is identical \u2014 you write it once and any MCP client can consume it. The client handles the transport, the handshake, and the format conversion for its specific LLM."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}